<P>
   RAC-DERBY (Louisville, Ky.) _ Leadall on the 125th Kentucky
Derby. By Joseph Durso.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Editors: Sidebars as warranted to be filed after the race &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   RAC-TRACKS-FUTURE (Louisville) _ Beneath the twin spires of
Churchill Downs, where tradition and history were being served
again Saturday in the 125th Kentucky Derby, the winds of change
were rustling and maybe even howling as thoroughbred racing groped
for new business alliances and mergers to save the sport from
oblivion in the 21st century. (Moved)
</P>
<P>
   RAC-ARATON-COLUMN (Louisville) _ Sports of the Times column on
the Kentucky Derby. The recent death of Charlie Whittingham meant
that an old guard of trainers was gone _ the many semi-anonymous
men who came to the Derby only when they had that one horse they
thought could win. Now trainers like Baffert, Lukas and Zito follow
the models of Disney and Murdoch, bringing in waves of horses and
turning themselves into media-savvy businessmen. By Harvey Araton.
(Moved)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BASEBALL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BBN-VECSEY-COLUMN (New York) _ Sports of the Times column on the
1969 Mets, who are being honored Sunday on Old-Timer's Day at Shea
Stadium. By George Vecsey. (Moved)
</P>
<P>
   BBO-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ Baseball notebook. Lead Item: Some of
the top closers, including Trevor Hoffman, John Wetteland and Rod
Beck, have been having a rough time in the season's early going. By
Murray Chass. (Moved)
</P>
<P>
   BBN-METS-GIANTS (New York) _ San Francisco at Mets, 1:40 p.m. By
Judy Battista
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BASKETBALL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BKN-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ The Allen Iverson-Shaquille O'Neal
battle for the scoring is overshadowed by their teams' struggle for
playoff position. By Mike Wise. (Moved)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-KNICKS (Undated) _ An unsettled team full of players with
their own agendas, rocked by management chaos and criticism in the
news media, has found its own odd and fragile brand of chemistry in
the season's last weeks. It has happened because players have
finally accepted their situations _ Marcus Camby and Latrell
Sprewell know they won't start, Allan Houston knows he has to
co-exist with Sprewell _ and, perhaps, because Patrick Ewing has
been sidelined. By Selena Roberts. (Moved)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FOOTBALL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FBN-ELWAY (Undated) _ As John Elway's career comes to an end,
other quarterbacks and other teams will scramble to fill the void
he leaves. (Moved)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-ANDERSON-COLUMN (Undated) _ As the Denver Broncos'
quarterback in three embarrassing Super Bowl losses, it was as if
John Elway had a tattoo that read, ``Can't win the big one.'' Never
mind that the Broncos were not the better team on any of those
three Sundays, he was the losing quarterback. And the losing
quarterback always gets the blame. But all that blame kept John
Elway playing when his battered body would have preferred to
surrender. (Moved)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ Lead Item: Bill Belichick, the Jets'
assistant head coach, declined to talk to other teams in the market
for a head coach this off season _ a strong sign that next season
will be Parcells's last as Jets coach. By Mike Freeman. (Moved)
</P>
