<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, May 2, and thereafter. For questions about stories, contact
Stewart Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   ABSENT-COUNCIL (Los Angeles) _ With no penalty for absences or
cut in their $107,000-a-year salaries, Los Angeles City Council
members missed between two and 21 weeks of council meetings last
year, and some routinely skipped important committee meetings, a
review of city records shows. By Deborah Sullivan. (Will move in
the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
