<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GLF-SENIOR02-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Jacobs feeling `more accepted'
 &HT;    By Glenn Sheeley
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Of all the Senior PGA Tour players feeling some form
of comfort zone at this week's Nationwide Championship at The Golf
Club of Georgia, nobody should come close to John Jacobs.
</P>
<P>
   No matter what else Jacobs accomplishes on the Senior Tour,
Alpharetta always will be the site of his official arrival. It was
here last year that Jacobs went from being ``a great guy who hits
it out of sight'' to ``legitimate winner,'' and glasses of wine
properly were sipped in celebration.
</P>
<P>
   With a one-shot win over Hale Irwin, who in 1998 was still
nearly unbeatable when near the lead, Jacobs became an enthusiastic
member of the club.
</P>
<P>
   ``I feel a little more accepted now,'' he said. ``Unless you
win, you're kind of like second class. . . . If you pound around,
pound around and don't win, there's always a doubt that gets in
your mind. The longer you go, there's more and more doubt.''
</P>
<P>
   More commonly referred to as ``JJ,'' Jacobs opened the 1999
season with a win in the MasterCard Championship in Hawaii, then
nearly grabbed another victory, eventually losing to Gary McCord in
an exciting playoff at the Toshiba Classic on March 14.
</P>
<P>
   Beyond the Jacobs reunion, new names are the theme at this
year's Nationwide. Rookie Bruce Fleisher has won three times and
leads the money list with $827,550. LaGrange's Allen Doyle, known
in Georgia for his six state titles as an amateur, has won twice,
including the recent PGA Seniors Championship, and is second on the
money list with $725,924. Marietta's Larry Nelson is third with
$543,228.
</P>
<P>
   McCord, Marietta's Joe Inman and Bob Duval, who won his first
tournament on the same day son David won The Players Championship,
also are in the Nationwide field.
</P>
<P>
   Irwin and Gil Morgan are the Senior Tour's mystery duo this
year. After dominating the last few years, they are 24th and 27th,
respectively on the money list.
</P>
<P>
   Although Irwin won the Senior Skins Game in January, he has only
one top 10 in a full-field event.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
