<P>
   OUTDOORS
</P>
<P>
   BILLFISH _ The chairman of the National Marine Fisheries Service
billfish advisory panel says the recently completed management plan
for Atlantic billfish will ``do absolutely nothing'' to reduce
mortality or rebuild stocks of sailfish and marlin because it does
not substantively deal with longline bycatch, or the unintentional
killing of billfish by longliners. The National Coalition for
Marine Conservation is calling for a 10-mile length limit and
six-hour maximum soak time for longlines. NMFS says it is studying
the length and soak-time restrictions. (Howard, Palm Beach Post)
15. MOVED
</P>
