<SLUG> BC-NY-FIRE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
3 ARE KILLED IN LONG ISLAND APARTMENT FIRE  
(DW)
</HEADLINE>
   c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Three people were killed and 13 others injured early Saturday in
a fire in a small apartment building in Huntington Station, N.Y.,
Suffolk County police and fire officials reported.
</P>
<P>
   The blaze, which broke out shortly after 3:30 a.m., badly
damaged all five apartments in the two-story building at 28 West
Hills Road, before members of the Huntington Manor Fire Department
were able to bring the flames under control three hours later. An
estimated 30 people were left homeless.
</P>
<P>
   The Suffolk County Police arson and homicide squads were
investigating because fatalities occurred and because the fire's
cause was unknown, according to Officer Sonny Di Stefano, a police
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   Di Stefano said the dead had been identified as Maria Chicas,
35, and her daughter, Maria, 4, who lived in a second-floor
apartment, and Luis Cruz, 37.
</P>
<P>
   Another resident, Elvancia Flores, 40, who suffered critical
injuries, was airlifted to the University Medical Center at Stony
Brook. Ten residents and two firefighters sustained
non-life-threatening injuries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
