   VETS-SYNDROME _ WASHINGTON - Department of Veterans Affairs
officials are trying to determine why at least 40 veterans of the
Persian Gulf war appear to have come down with amyotrophic lateral
sclerosis (ALS), the nerve disease sometimes called ``Lou Gehrig's
Disease.'' A University of Kentucky neurologist who specializes in
treating ALS said he was asked by VA officials to review medical
records of Gulf veterans diagnosed with the disease and will ask
the Defense Department this week to fund a study to determine how
many other veterans whose names do not appear in VA records also
