<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Love ya, blue
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ The Dodgers clubhouse has spit its first bolt. Raul
Mondesi was demoted from the clean-up spot after hitting .143 with
runners in scoring position. His response: hitting a two-run homer
from the No. 5 hole to let Kevin Brown beat Milwaukee 3-2 on
Tuesday _ then Mondesi ripped management.
</P>
<P>
   ``How come they have to change me?'' Mondesi griped. ``We have
nine players. How come I'm always the one who has to change? This
happens to me every year. Every year, it's the same crap. I'm tired
of it.''
</P>
<P>
   That's not manager Davey Johnson's only flashfire. Brown
wrenched his back fielding a Fernando Vina bunt that game. The $105
Million Man already has given up five homers this spring. Last year
in San Diego, Brown yielded just eight homers in 257 innings.
</P>
<P>
   HI, PAL
</P>
<P>
   How long did it take Boston's Rheal Cormier and Cleveland's Jim
Thome to make up after Cormier plunked the Cleveland first baseman
last Saturday and started a brawl? About as long as it takes to
drive downtown from Fenway Park.
</P>
<P>
   Cormier, a hunting buddy of Thome, saw him waiting for a cab
after the game and gave him a lift to the Indians' hotel while they
patched things up.
</P>
<P>
   Cormier, a hockey player growing up in New Brunswick, Canada,
said, ``He came over to me and said, 'No hard feelings, it's part
of the game.' So yeah, I gave him a ride back to his hotel.''
</P>
<P>
   HE'S NO. 1
</P>
<P>
   Mike Morgan is trying to fight his way off one of the game's
most dubious lists. Having set the major-league record this spring
by pitching for his 11th different club, Morgan also is attempting
to remove himself from atop the standings for the game's lowest
career winning percentage. He's 4-1 with the Rangers. The lowest
percentages, with a minimum 250 career decisions:
</P>
<P>
   Pitcher _ Record _ Win % _ Seasons active
</P>
<P>
   Pedro Ramos _ 117-160 _ .422 _ 1955-70
</P>
<P>
   Mike Morgan _ 125-170 _ .422 _ 1978-
</P>
<P>
   Long Tom Hughes _ 132-174 _ .431 _ 1900-13
</P>
<P>
   Win Mercer _ 131-164 _ .444 _ 1898-1902
</P>
<P>
   Ned Garver _ 129-157 _ .451 _ 1948-61
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
