DIRT (Phoenix) _ Dirt, yes that gritty stuff people wipe off their
shoes, is a hot commodity in Phoenix's booming construction market.
Those who don't have it want it so they can build homes, offices,
shopping centers and highways, and those who have too much of it
need to get rid of it to clear sites and finish developments. The
going rate is $3 to $5 a cubic yard. By CATHERINE REAGOR. Story
will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
